<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:01PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Morgan
and northeastern Adams Counties through 445 PM MDT...
At 400 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hoyt, or 22 miles southwest of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hoyt, Twelve-Mile Corner, Adena School and Adena.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
